 Inf Rgt DUI.png|40px]]\n|[[505th Infantry Regiment (United States)|505th Infantry Regiment]] [[Distinctive Unit Insignia]]\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:ASU overseas service bar.jpg|50px]]\n|8 [[Overseas Service Bar]]s\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:German Armed Forces Badge for Military Proficiency.jpg|60px]]\n|[[German Armed Forces Badge for Military Proficiency]] in bronze\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:Fallschirmspringerabzeichen der Bundeswehr in Bronze.jpg|100px]]\n|[[Awards and decorations of the German Armed Forces|German Parachutist badge in bronze]]\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:Canadian jump wings.png|100px]]\n|Canadian Jump Wings (red maple leaf)\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:Wings badge.JPG|100px]]\n|British Parachutist Badge\n|-\n| align=center | [[File:IrishSilver.jpg|100px]]\n|Irish Parachutist Badge in silver\n|}\n|}\n\n===Other awards===\n\n* Honorary ROCK of the Year in 2008<ref name=\"statement\" />\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Biography}}\n{{commons category|William B. Caldwell, IV}}\n* [[International Security Assistance Force]]\n* [[Combined Security Transition Command \u2013 Afghanistan]]\n* [[2009 congressional delegation to Afghanistan]]\n\n==Notes and reference==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Caldwell, William B}}\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Columbus, Georgia]]\n[[Category:Military personnel from Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:American army personnel of the Iraq War]]\n[[Category:American army personnel of the War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)]]\n[[Category:United States Army generals]]\n[[Category:John F. Kennedy School of Government alumni]]\n[[Category:United States Military Academy alumni]]\n[[Category:Commandants of the United States Army Command and General Staff College]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Legion of Merit]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Defense Superior Service Medal]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Defense Distinguished Service Medal]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the P