{"title_page": "Charles Bowman (accountant)", "text_new": "{{short description|British accountant|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n<!-- Deleted imag[[File:Charles Bowman, Lord Mayor of the City of London (2017-2018).jpg|thumb|Charles Bowman, 690th Lord Mayor of the City of London]] -->\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | name               = Sir Charles Bowman\n | honorific_suffix   = {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KStJ|JP}}\n|order        = 690th\n|office       = Lord Mayor of London\n|1blankname   = [[Mayor of London|Metropolitan Mayor]]\n|1namedata    = [[Sadiq Khan]]\n|term_start   = 10 November 2017\n|term_end     = 9 November 2018\n|predecessor  = [[Andrew Parmley|Sir Andrew Parmley]]\n|successor    = [[Peter Estlin]]\n | birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1961}}\n|birth_name = Charles Edward Beck Bowman\n | birth_place        = Essex\n | death_date         =\n | death_place        = \n|occupation         = [[Chartered accountant]]\n|alma_mater         = [[University of Bristol]]\n|spouse = Samantha Bowman\n}}\n\n'''Sir Charles Edward Beck Bowman''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KStJ|JP}} (born 1961) is a British accountant who served as the 690th [[Lord Mayor of London]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Haslett|first1=Emma|title=The City of London has elected its 690th Lord Mayor|url=http://www.cityam.com/272971/city-london-has-elected-its-690th-lord-mayor|accessdate=23 January 2018|work=City A.M.|date=29 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=mayorbiog>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/about-the-city/the-lord-mayor/Pages/biography.aspx|website=City of London|accessdate=2018-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Waller|first1=Martin|title=The man who must shepherd the City through some of its most testing times|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-man-who-must-shepherd-the-city-through-some-of-its-most-testing-times-bqfk0jpjs|accessdate=23 January 2018|work=The Times|date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nAs Lord Mayor, Bowman launched the [[City of London Corporation|City of London]] a corporation's Business of Trust programme. This programme seeks to create \"a lasting legacy of better business, trusted by society\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Lord Mayor architect of business trust in a modern City|url=https://www.icaew.com/en/groups-and-networks/local-groups-and-societies/london-ds/london-accountant/features/dec17-new-lord-mayor|website=ICAEW|accessdate=23 January 2018|date=December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Fantato|first1=Damian|title=Lord Mayor pushes trust in financial services|url=https://www.ftadviser.com/your-industry/2017/11/29/lord-mayor-pushes-trust-in-financial-services/|accessdate=23 January 2018|date=29 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Davy|first1=Jo|title=Lord Mayor: No magic fix for trust problems|url=http://www.citymatters.london/lord-mayor-no-magic-fix-for-business-of-trust/|accessdate=23 January 2018|work=City Matters|date=22 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nBowman joined [[PwC]] in September 1983. He qualified as a chartered accountant in 1986 and was admitted to partnership in 1995.<ref>{{cite web|title=Charles Bowman|url=https://www.pwc.co.uk/contacts/c/charles-bowman.html|publisher=PWC|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nBowman has specialised in delivering audit and capital market transaction services to large listed and multi-national companies. Among his various leadership roles, he has led PwC's Building Public Trust programme.<ref>{{cite web|title=Trust matters|url=https://www.pwc.co.uk/build-public-trust/trust-matters.html|publisher=PWC|accessdate=23 January 2018|quote=Contacts {{!}} Charles Bowman {{!}} Partner}}</ref>\n\n== City of London ==\nHe is an [[Alderman]] of the Lime Street Ward and served as [[Sheriff]] of the City of London in 2015\u201316.\n\nBowman is a member of the Court of the [[Worshipful Company of Grocers]] and a liveryman of the [[Worshipful Company of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Rt. Hon. the Lord Mayor, Charles Edward Beck Bowman (Alderman)|url=http://democracy.cityoflondon.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=1261|website=City of London|accessdate=23 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe was appointed [[Order of Saint John (chartered 1888)|Knight of the Order of St John]] in January 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/notice/2942003|title=Order of St John|website=www.thegazette.co.uk|access-date=2018-02-07}}</ref> and was [[Knight Bachelor|knighted]] in the [[2019 Birthday Honours]] for services to trust in business, international trade and the City of London.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=62666|supp=y|page=B2|date=8 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe is married to Samantha, a veterinary surgeon and liveryman of the [[Worshipful Company of Woolmen]]. They have two daughters, Grace and Charlotte.<ref name=mayorbiog/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-civ}}\n{{s-bef| before = [[Andrew Parmley|Sir Andrew Parmley]]}} \n{{s-ttl|title=[[Lord Mayor of London]]|years=2017\u20132018}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Peter Estlin]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bowman, Charles}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Uppingham School]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Bristol]]\n[[Category:Knights Bachelor]]\n[[Category:British accountants]]\n[[Category:21st-century lord mayors of London]]\n[[Category:21st-century British politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century English politicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British accountant|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n<!-- Deleted imag[[File:Charles Bowman, Lord Mayor of the City of London (2017-2018).jpg|thumb|Charles Bowman, 690th Lord Mayor of the City of London]] -->\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | name               = Sir Charles Bowman\n | honorific_suffix   = {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KStJ|JP}}\n|order        = 690th\n|office       = Lord Mayor of London\n|1blankname   = [[Mayor of London|Metropolitan Mayor]]\n|1namedata    = [[Sadiq Khan]]\n|term_start   = 10 November 2017\n|term_end     = 9 November 2018\n|predecessor  = [[Andrew Parmley|Sir Andrew Parmley]]\n|successor    = [[Peter Estlin]]\n | birth_date         = {{birth year and age|1961}}\n|birth_name = Charles Edward Beck Bowman\n | birth_place        = Essex\n | death_date         =\n | death_place        = \n|occupation         = [[Chartered accountant]]\n|alma_mater         = [[University of Bristol]]\n|spouse = Samantha Bowman\n}}\n\n'''Sir Charles Edward Beck Bowman''' {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|KStJ|JP}} (born 1961) is a British accountant who served as the 690th [[Lord Mayor of London]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Haslett|first1=Emma|title=The City of London has elected its 690th Lord Mayor|url=http://www.cityam.com/272971/city-london-has-elected-its-690th-lord-mayor|accessdate=23 January 2018|work=City A.M.|date=29 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=mayorbiog>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/about-the-city/the-lord-mayor/Pages/biography.aspx|website=City of London|accessdate=2018-05-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Waller|first1=Martin|title=The man who must shepherd the City through some of its most testing times|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/the-man-who-must-shepherd-the-city-through-some-of-its-most-testing-times-bqfk0jpjs|accessdate=23 January 2018|work=The Times|date=11 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nAs Lord Mayor, Bowman launched the [[City of London Corporation|City of London]] a corporation's Business of Trust programme. This programme seeks to create \"a lasting legacy of better business, trusted by society\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Lord Mayor architect of business trust in a modern City|url=https://www.icaew.com/en/groups-and-networks/local-groups-and-societies/london-ds/london-accountant/features/dec17-new-lord-mayor|website=ICAEW|accessdate=23 January 2018|date=December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Fantato|first1=Damian|title=Lord Mayor pushes trust in financial services|url=https://www.ftadviser